commentary: Mohammed Shami to Hetmyer, OUT foxed by the slower ball! Change up, pitched up, and he looks to flog this towards midwicket. The ball was an off-cutter, and it grips and slows up after pitching. He swings, misses and hears the death-rattle behind him. This could turn out to be a blessing in disguise, as neither Hope nor Hetmyer have been able to get a move-on, despite having just completed a 50-run partnership
